Eastman, Joseph T. Field and lab notebooks from J. T. Eastman's work on Antarctic fishes.

Eastman, Joseph T. Green Record book from Federal Supply Service labeled "NBP 96-6". Contains field data from the R/V Nathaniel B. Palmer, Cruise 96-6. Lyttelton, NZ- McMurdo 11 Dec 1996-8 Jan 1997. Contains specimen data from Antarctic fishes at McMurdo. Includes histology of specimens. There are inter-mixed blank pages, but the entire book is used.

Eastman, Joseph T. Black and red ledger labeled "LMG 01-05". Contains data from the ARSV Laurence M. Gould, Cruise 01-05, 11 June-16 July 2001. Punta Arenas. Fishing near Palmer Station, Brabant Island and Low Island. Includes data on bouyancy and morphology. Microfil procedures and Alizarin staining. There are many blank pages.

Eastman, Joseph T. Black and red ledger labeled "NBP 04-04, ICEFISH Cruise". Contains data from NBP 04-04 ICEFISH Cruise 17 May 2004-17 July 2004 Punta Arenas to Cape Town. Contains notes on stations and localities as well as Microfil data for Eleginops and others. Includes data on specimens skeletonized.

Eastman, Joseph T. Black and red ledger labeled "NBP 04-04 ICEFISH Histology". Data from the NBP 04-04 ICEFISH Cruise, Histology Results. Includes data on a variety of taxa collected and examined histologically. Several references to photographs.
Eastman, Joseph T. Notebook entitled "Fishes #2". Contains fish data from Antarctica. Dates are in the 1960's and 1970's.
Eastman, Joseph T. Notebook entitled "Fishes #1". Contains some fish data from Antarctica. The remainder of the book contains data on fishes from elsewhere. Dates are in 1974.

Eastman, Joseph T. Ledger (notebook) containing data on fishes from Antarctica including mostly dates in the 1980's. Many blank pages are intermixed, but the full ledger appears to be used. Includes morphological data from specimens at National Museum of New Zealand and the University of Michigan.

Eastman, Joseph T. Green Record book from Federal Supply Service labeled "McMurdo- 1986". Includes morphological and specimen data from Antarctic fishes at McMurdo. Some information on hystology is included, such as the stains used and which specimens are sectioned. Book is blank after page 143.

Eastman, Joseph T. Green field book from Federal Supply Service labeled "McMurdo 1991" with logo of Antarctica and a penguin on the cover. Includes specimen data, histology notes, tissue freezing experiments and observations on aquarium specimens at McMurdo. Pages after 117 are blank.

Eastman, Joseph T. Green field book from Federal Supply Service labeled "Eastman McMurdo 1995". Includes buoyancy data and histology technique data for several taxa of Antarctic fishes as well as data for specimens perfused with either Bouin's solution or Microfil. Pages after 49 are blank.

Eastman, Joseph T. Black and red ledger labeled "NBP 97-9 Ross Sea". Includes data from the NBP Cruise 97-9, 20 December 1997-10 Jan 1998 of the Southwestern Ross Sea, ice edge to McMurdo. 2nd Roaverrs Cruise. Bouyancy data are included. Includes detailed drawings of sampling locations and drawings of stingrays and fish fins as illustrations of morphology.

Eastman, Joseph T. Black and red ledger labeled "Research, 2003-2010 Histology". Includes histology data on a variety of specimens of Antarctic fishes. Includes drawings and references to photographs. Many blank pages intermixed, but the entire book is used.
